[[[description]]]
Checks whether a [zval](https://phpinternals.net/docs/zval) is copyable (see the [`IS_TYPE_COPYABLE`](https://phpinternals.net/docs/is_type_copyable) type). The [`Z_COPYABLE`](https://phpinternals.net/docs/z_copyable) macro may also be used for this.

[[[additional_information]]]
This macro also has a counterpart macro, `Z_OPT_COPYABLE_P`, that accepts a pointer to a zval instead.
